The paper discusses content-based image retrieval (CBIR) using local descriptors (SIFT) and convolutional neural networks (CNN), which are both commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on instance retrieval, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different methods, which involves machine learning and optimization, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the use of CNNs, which is a popular topic in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
